  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 47a621783cb453147b01764dde5ed130, type: 3}
  m_Name: 1_MagicIntro
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  dialogueLines:
  - ...
  - You finally opened it...
  - Do not be frightened, dear.
  - I am gone from the living world... but this cottage still remembers me.
  - As long as the moon door remains open, I can stay here and guide you.
  - What lies beyond that door is the hidden side of the world.
  - A place sustained by moonlight and old magic.
  - Long ago, magic existed everywhere. Humans lived alongside magical creatures
    without fear.
  - But belief faded. And with it, magic began to weaken.
  - The last Moonwardens bound the magical world to the moon to preserve what remained.
  - That is why the lands only awaken at night... Moonlight keeps the magic alive.
  - This cottage exists between worlds, neither fully magic nor fully human.
  - A place where both can still touch.
  - For generations, Moonwardens cared for this balance.
  - We nurtured the land and protected the old magic from fading entirely.
  - Now the responsibility belongs to you... The magic here is weak, but not beyond
    saving.
  - As you restore the land, the magical world will slowly grow stronger again.
  - To understand what's at stake, you should visit the enchanted forest...
  - Wait until moonlight hits the moon door, then you'll be able to enter and see
    for yourself...
  autoProgressLines: 01010101010101010101010101010101010100
